        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XDmaPs_SelfTest</definition>
        <argsstring>(XDmaPs *InstPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XDmaPs_SelfTest</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_dma_ps" kindref="compound">XDmaPs</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function runs a self-test on the driver and hardware device. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This self test performs a local loopback and verifies data can be sent and received.</para><para>The time for this test is proportional to the baud rate that has been set prior to calling this function.</para><para>The mode and control registers are restored before return.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dma_ps" kindref="compound">XDmaPs</ref> instance</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><verbatim>    - XST_SUCCESS if the test was successful
    - XST_FAILURE if the test failed
</verbatim></para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
This function can hang if the hardware is not functioning properly. </para>        </detaileddescription>
